originalText.text: Reserved a spot for $60 during the car show. When we came back for the car, the guy wanted an additional $20 to get the vehicle out. He swears he told me specifically that it happened. That was never said and makes zero sense. Then he wanted to get attitude. Stay away. Scammers.

originalText.text: I took the NYS Bar for two days at the Javits Center. I parked my car in the garage. The men at the garage were so nice to me. The Bar barely gave us 30 minutes lunch. I stored a cooler in my trunk to save time. The men at the garage walked me to my car so I could retrieve my lunch . The older bald guy also provided me with an aspirin after I did the morning session of the Bar and wasn't feeling well. I totally didn't get their names, but the older men who work here went above and beyond for me. As for payment,  I got a great discount using Spothero. I highly recommend these high quality human beings. Someone give these guys a raise.

hinestly one of the worst experiences so far, if. i could rats this place at a zero i would, arrived early so i could avoid the extra charge but because the employees left the register with nobody to check us out we ended up having to pay a fee of 30 extra dollars because they couldnt do their job right, and after paying the fee proceded to have to wait for another 2 hours for someone to even talk to us after we tried talking to every employee, most employees ignored us entirely and only ONE actually gave us a reason, and after that he got our car within 15 min! what was so hard about that ???

TLDR :dont bother with this place they will have you waiting for hours for nothing and when asked about it will completely ignore you
